Files:
- e2e/side-panel-theme.e2e.ts (same file as US-001)

Context:
`useTheme` persists to `chrome.storage.local` under key `'theme'`. On mount, it reads from storage and applies the class. This is the same hydration pattern as accordion state â€” the theme should be correct on first paint.

Test approach:
```typescript
let sidePanel = await openSidePanel(context);

// Switch to dark mode
await sidePanel.getByLabel('Switch to dark mode').click();
await expect(sidePanel.locator('html')).toHaveClass(/dark/);

// Close and reopen
await sidePanel.close();
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
sidePanel = await openSidePanel(context);

// Verify dark mode persisted
await expect(sidePanel.locator('html')).toHaveClass(/dark/, { timeout: 5_000 });
await expect(sidePanel.getByLabel('Switch to light mode')).toBeVisible();
```
